<h2 id="best-practices">Best practices</h2>
<p><strong>Use concise, accurate, and specific labels.</strong> Avoid vague and abstract language like &quot;Get started&quot; or &quot;Learn more&quot;. Prefer explicit labels instead, like &quot;Find doctor&quot; or &quot;Schedule appointment&quot;. Accurate and specific language improves user confidence and engagement (<a href="https://www.nngroup.com/articles/information-scent/#:~:text=Perhaps%20the%20most,to%20click%20it." title="Information Scent: How Users Decide Where to Go Next - Nielsen Norman Group">1</a>), while overly broad calls to action can mislead, confuse, and fail to interest users (<a href="https://www.nngroup.com/articles/get-started/" title="Get Started Stops Users - Nielsen Norman Group">2</a>).</p>
<p><strong>Use sentence case.</strong> All-uppercase text is slower and more difficult to read (<a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/low-vision-needs/#capitalization">3</a>). Furthermore, screen readers sometimes interpret certain uppercased words as common initialisms (such as ADD or US), and may erroneously spell out those words letter by letter (<a href="https://webaim.org/techniques/screenreader/#:~:text=Screen%20readers%20try%20to%20pronounce%20acronyms%2C%20if%20there%20are%20sufficient%20vowels/consonants%20to%20be%20pronounceable.%20Otherwise%2C%20they%20spell%20out%20the%20letters.">4</a>).</p>
<h2 id="usage">Usage</h2>
<h3 id="secondary-buttons">Secondary buttons</h3>
<p>De-emphasized buttons pair well with primary buttons or in interfaces that need to be decluttered. They can be created with the <a href="#variant-attribute"><code>variant</code> attribute</a>.</p>

{% embed "@tc/includes/example.twig" %}
{% block content %}
<button is="tcds-ui-button" variant="secondary">Secondary button</button>
{% endblock %}
{% endembed %}


<p><strong>Note:</strong> Because secondary buttons automatically have a right-facing caret button, avoid using additional icons with this variant.</p>
<h3 id="link-buttons">Link buttons</h3>
<p>Links can be styled to look like buttons with the <code>tcds-link-button</code> extension for the <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/a"><code>a</code> element</a>.</p>

{% embed "@tc/includes/example.twig" %}
{% block content %}
<a is="tcds-link-button" href="https://www.texaschildrens.org/">Go to texaschildrens.org</a>
{% endblock %}
{% endembed %}


<h3 id="icons">Icons</h3>
<p><a href="/brand/icons">Icons</a> can be added to a button by nesting the <a href="/components/icon">icon component</a>. Use them sparingly, as too many icons can create too much visual noise. Never use more than one icon per button.</p>

{% embed "@tc/includes/example.twig" %}
{% block content %}
<button is="tcds-ui-button">
  <tcds-icon icon="download"></tcds-icon> Download
</button>
{% endblock %}
{% endembed %}


<p>Descendant order determines the icon&#39;s alignment.</p>

{% embed "@tc/includes/example.twig" %}
{% block content %}
<button is="tcds-ui-button">
  Next <tcds-icon icon="arrow-right"></tcds-icon>
</button>
{% endblock %}
{% endembed %}


